&lt;h1&gt;RUH Employees Only&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Respiratory Developmental Medical Nurse Practitioner - Band 6&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to Maternity leave an exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit a Band 6 developmental Respiratory Medical Nurse Practitioner on a fixed term part time basis. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is an experienced and motivated Respiratory nurse to join the Medical Team as a developmental Medical Nurse Practitioner.  The successful candidate will have the opportunity to develop their skills, under the supervision of the existing team for MNP’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is for 18.75 hours per week, for a fixed term of 9 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be looking to move to a more autonomous role, and starting to make higher level decisions relating to patient treatment and care.  The successful candidate will work as part of a team of MNP’s and medical staff.  You will need to be self motivated with excellent communication skills and a passion to work in Respiratory medicine. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Senior Medical Nurse Practitioner Shelley Meiklereid.&lt;/p&gt;
